   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER THREE THE ISSUE OF GOD THE SPIRIT'S DISPENSING SPEAKING FORTH</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE APPLICATION OF GOD'S ACCOMPLISHED PURPOSE Scripture Reading: Eph 1:13-14</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Hymns: #539, #493</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>OUTLINE In sealing the believers v. 13: As the compound, anointing, life-giving, and indwelling Spirit promised by God.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Through the believers' hearing of the word of the truth, the gospel of their salvation v. 13a.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Through the believers' believing in Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To saturate the believers continuously unto the redemption of their body Eph 4:30.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>For transforming the believers into a treasure to God as His inheritance Eph 1:11; 2 Cor 3:18: By His renewing Titus 3:5; Rom 12:2b.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>With the life element of the all-inclusive Christ Phil 1:19b.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>To make the believers a mark of God's image 2 Cor 3:18b: With the substance of God.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>For the expression of God.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>In pledging to the believers v. 14a: Through the sealing.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>As a foretaste of God.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>For a guarantee of God as our inheritance.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Unto the redemption of the body of the believers as God's acquired possession.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>To the praise of God's glory v. 14b: In the expression of God's image.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>In the enjoyment of God's riches.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The dispensing of the Divine Trinity issuing in the Body of Christ as the organic constitution Eph 4:4-6 with: God the Father as the source.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>God the Son as the element.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>God the Spirit as the essence.</S>
   </TEXT>
